headline: Why Gilead Sciences Stock Slipped Today
summary: Gilead Sciences (NASDAQ: GILD) didn't have a bad first quarter, but investors didn't find it inspiring either.  For the period, Gilead's revenue clocked in at $6.67 billion, essentially flat over the same quarter of 2024.  This was offset by improvements in liver disease and human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) medications.
